  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNHCR activities in Myanmar, 2014-2015</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNHCR plays an active and leading role in Myanmar, especially in the Rakhine State, in order to coordinate the management and operation of the many camps for internally displaced persons, including the provision of &apos;shelters&apos; and the distribution of the basic relief items. UNHCR also has the leading role in a rights-based protection of internally displaced persons, and work closely with Danish Refugee Council in relation to efforts for internal displaced people in the Rakhine State. UNHCR has a total requirement of about 463 million DKK for their efforts to IDPs in Myanmar and the Myanmar refugees in Thailand. The request, which covers the needs in 2014, is met by 25 per cent. The Danish contribution of 10 million DKK for 2014-15 is given unearmarked to UNHCR&apos;s humanitarian activities both in Myanmar and Thailand.</narrative>
  </description>
